INSERT INTO `work_togethers` VALUES (2,'Haidar Alamir','haidar@xonboard.io','71885711','test','forms/1710405811_dummy.pdf','forms/1710405811_dummy.pdf','2024-03-14 08:43:31','2024-03-14 08:43:31'),(3,'Mohamed Oubibi','oubibi@bnu.edu.cn','008615948728389','Dr. Mohamed Oubibi is a lecturer and research fellow at the Smart Learning Institute of Beijing Normal University and a visiting professor at Rattana Bundit University (Thailand). He received his Ph.D. in Educational Technology from Northeast Normal University (China) and a Postdoc at Zhejiang Normal University (China). His research interests include Smart education, AI, AR, VR, ICT in education, teacher competencies, and Educational technology.','forms/1718370656_CV-Mohamed-Oubibi.pdf','forms/1718370656_CV-Mohamed-Oubibi.pdf','2024-06-14 13:10:56','2024-06-14 13:10:56'),(4,'Amr Eleraqi','amr.eleraqi.ca@gmail.com','0016475109850','At the intersection of data science and public policy, my work with IDSC harnesses advanced NLP to elevate decision-making. Leading a project that improved team productivity by 60%, I\'ve demonstrated a commitment to innovation and efficiency.\r\n\r\nAs an educator, I impart knowledge on AI and data analysis, further enriching my expertise. My consultancy experience, developing KPI dashboards, has been pivotal in boosting operational efficiency by 30%, showcasing my proficiency in data storytelling and statistical analysis.','forms/1722184533_resume_Amreleraqi.docx','forms/1722184533_resume_Amreleraqi.docx','2024-07-28 16:35:33','2024-07-28 16:35:33'),(5,'Harry McKenzie','harrymckenzie11@icloud.com','+44 7864 273470','Harry McKenzie is a hardworking and creative individual with strong analytical and interpersonal skills. He is interested in the intersection of diplomacy, particularly in the MENA region, and AI and speaks four languages to a high-level. He studies Arabic and Spanish at the University of St Andrews where he is achieving a high 1st-class grade, ranking first in Spanish in 2023 and excelling as the top year-abroad candidate. He is currently studying Arabic at the Qasid Institute in Jordan while taking the Blue Dot AI Safety Fundamentals course.\r\n\r\nHarry has gained extensive professional experience through his internship with the Labour Middle East Council (LMEC), where he produces weekly MENA briefings for Labour MPs and key stakeholders. His consulting work includes producing research and communications for an African elections campaign. At university, he created a speaker series attended by over 400 people, engaging with prominent figures such as HRH the Saudi Ambassador to the UK. As co-leader of the Effective Altruism St Andrews group, he piloted new programs involving 60 students. In his free time, Harry enjoys being disappointed by his favourite football team and listening to Abdel Halim Hafez.','forms/1731779281_CV October \'24.pdf','forms/1731779281_MENA AI Observatory Cover Letter.pdf','2024-11-16 17:48:01','2024-11-16 17:48:01'),(6,'Sam Obeidat','sam@Waiu.org','6198162359','I’ve trained over 32,000 professionals across 12+ sectors, crafted 35+ AI strategies for governments and corporations, and built a solid track record of scaling companies and developing high-impact AI products. As the founder of The AI Citizen movement, with over 50,000 members, I’m raising awareness about how AI is reshaping business, job markets, and the future of humanity. I lead a team of scientists and engineers at World AI X Ventures, creating transformative solutions in finance, education, healthcare, and defense. I also host the Chief AI Officer (CAIO) Program at the World AI X University, equipping executives to thrive in the AI era, and serve as a professor at several universities. My mission is to empower organizations with practical AI frameworks and models, and I’m eager to bring this expertise to the Forbes Technology Council to inspire collaboration and innovation.','forms/1737178324_Sam_Obeidat_CAIO_Resume+Revised.pdf','forms/1737178324_MENAOBSAI - WAIX Collaboration.pdf','2025-01-18 05:32:04','2025-01-18 05:32:04'),(7,'Lina Hajjar','linahajjar1@hotmail.com','+4551772001','Founder and CEO of AI-Dev Solutions: https://www.aidevsolutions.dk/ a Danish AI initiative focused on developing responsible, pedagogy-aligned artificial intelligence systems for education and small businesses. With a background in mathematics and more than a decade of teaching experience, I specialize in bridging advanced AI technologies with structured learning design.\r\n\r\nI am currently leading the development of MathAI: an AI-powered tutoring platform built on a retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) architecture. The system integrates curriculum-aligned knowledge mapping, adaptive progression models, output validation layers, and hallucination mitigation mechanisms to ensure safe and transparent use in school environments. \r\n\r\nMy work focuses on the responsible deployment of AI in K–12 education, including issues related to model reliability, bias mitigation, pedagogical integrity, and governance frameworks. I advocate for AI systems that augment -not replace- teachers, and that operate within clearly defined ethical and regulatory boundaries.\r\n\r\nMy broader research and development interests include adaptive learning systems, AI safety layers for educational applications, explainability in large language model integrations, and cross-regional collaboration between European and MENA AI ecosystems.\r\n\r\nThrough AI-Dev Solutions, I work at the intersection of AI engineering, mathematics education, and responsible innovation, contributing to discussions on how AI can be implemented in ways that are technically robust, pedagogically sound, and socially accountable.','forms/1771592260_CV_Lina_engelsk.docx','forms/1771592260_Collaboration Details.pdf','2026-02-20 12:57:40','2026-02-20 12:57:40');
